\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Mean fixed-time condition balanced accuracy under the earlier baseline simulator and the richer simulator, both at adaptive \(60/20\) scale. The richer simulator still makes exact event prediction harder, but after the latest direct-condition refinements it now exposes a stronger separation between the best calibrated condition models and the weaker empirical baselines.}}{18}{figure.caption.10}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:baseline_richer_conditions}{{7}{18}{Mean fixed-time condition balanced accuracy under the earlier baseline simulator and the richer simulator, both at adaptive \(60/20\) scale. The richer simulator still makes exact event prediction harder, but after the latest direct-condition refinements it now exposes a stronger separation between the best calibrated condition models and the weaker empirical baselines}{figure.caption.10}{}}
